At the end of pregnancy, it feels like time slows down to almost a screeching halt. 
You're now simply in your baby's birth story.. 
It feels far away, but what's a few days or weeks when compared to the next year? 
Your baby will be in your arms soon & then time will ridiculously speed up. 
Take a deep breath & enjoy these last few moments🪽

latestPosts.caption:
It's daunting, knowing I'll never be her again.
The girl I was before I became a mum-

She had no idea that the last day of pregnancy was also the last day she'd ever be just her.
She feels like a stranger now. Familiar, but far away.
I look at photos of her and think, she had no idea what was coming. The love. The pain. The beauty. The fear. The breaking. The becoming. And sometimes, I miss her so deeply it hurts. But I wouldn't go back. Not even for a second.
I just wish I could hug her. Tell her it's going to be okay. That the woman she becomes is softer, stronger, and more needed than she ever imagined. 

I wish she could see us now.
Because she's extraordinary. 🦋
